    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1942-03-14T12:00:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1942-03-14T12:00:00-05:00" n="422"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d422">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">622.3531/2: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Ambassador in Ecuador</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Long</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Quito</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1942-03-14T12:00:00-05:00"
                            >March 14, 1942—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 7:37 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>198. The Argentine Government has made preliminary overtures looking to a barter
                    agreement which would involve supplying crude rubber from Ecuador in return for
                    authorizing exports of tires from Argentina. The Minister of Finance<note n="65"
                        xml:id="d422fn65">Vicente Illingworth.</note> desires an expression of
                    opinion as to the attitude of the United States to such an arrangement. Actually
                    Argentina and other buyers are offering higher prices for Ecuadoran rubber than
                    is being offered in the United States.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Long</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
